Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Fill and boil your #kettle{}, we will use it for the rice later. Meanwhile, remove the outer leaves from the @cauliflower{} and cut away the stem at the base. Quarter the cauliflower into four large wedges. In a #large mixing bowl{} mix together the @mayonnaise{2}, @tomato puree{15}, @smoked paprika{1} and a pinch of @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Add the cauliflower wedges to the spiced mayo and use your hands to make sure they are well covered. Tip the @panko breadcrumbs{30} onto the wedges and toss to coat evenly. Transfer the cauliflower onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{for the sauce} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until golden brown and crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}. 

> The cauliflower is cooked when you can easily slip a knife through.

Pour the @water{300} into a #large saucepan{} and bring back to the boil over high heat. Once boiling, stir in the @basmati rice{150} and @ground cumin{2} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from the heat and set aside (still covered) for another ~{10%minutes}.

> The rice will finish cooking in its own steam.

Meanwhile, drain the @sweetcorn{163} in a #sieve{}. Heat a #frying pan{} over high heat (no oil!). When hot, add the corn and fry, turning occasionally, until black spots start to appear, ~{3-5%minutes}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(stalks and all). Zest the @lime{1} and chop into wedges. Once the corn has charred, stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Remove from the heat.

Halve the @cherry plum tomatoes{100}. Slice lengthways into the @avocado{1}. Once you reach the stone turn the avocado around to cut it in half. Twist each half and pull it apart. Remove the stone then scoop out the insides and into squares. In a #large bowl{}, combine the corn, tomatoes, avocado, coriander, lime zest, a squeeze of lime juice (to taste), a good glug of @olive oil{for the salsa} and a pinch of @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

== Chipotle Drizzle ==

Make the chipotle drizzle by mixing together the @chipotle paste{10}, @olive oil{}(for the drizzle) and a squeeze of lime juice. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Serve up: Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}. Divide the rice, salsa and cauliflower between your plates. Serve with a little chipotle drizzle (to your taste, it's hot!) and any remaining wedges of lime. Enjoy!